&lt;p&gt;The Digital Systems &amp;amp; Operations Intern is the technical backbone of the OPEX function. This role owns the configuration, maintenance, and continuous improvement of the tools and data infrastructure that the entire operational excellence team — and, by extension, the institution — relies on every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be the go-to person for Asana, Google Workspace, Slack, and any AI-powered productivity tools deployed by the team. You will build and maintain dashboards, keep the project portfolio updated with real-time actuals, ensure the institutional knowledge base is clean and accessible, and identify opportunities to automate repetitive work. You will work closely with the IT team and the ETO to ensure tool configurations support operational goals rather than create friction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a role for someone who loves systems, moves fast, and finds genuine satisfaction in making things work better. If you have ever reorganized a chaotic shared drive and felt proud of it, this is your role.&lt;/p&gt;
