&lt;p&gt;The African Leadership University is currently hiring facilitators for its in-person&amp;nbsp;Self-Directed Learning Skills Lab. The role is designed for an education&amp;nbsp;professional with strong experience in higher education instruction, facilitation,&amp;nbsp;curriculum implementation, learning management systems, digital learning&amp;nbsp;tools, and student academic support.&lt;br&gt;The successful candidate will facilitate in-person sessions, update designed&amp;nbsp;lesson plans, curate self-work and student deliverables, and support Year 1&amp;nbsp;students in developing strong self-directed learning skills. The role requires&amp;nbsp;someone who can work across physical and digital learning environments,&amp;nbsp;ensuring that students are supported both inside the classroom and through&amp;nbsp;structured online learning platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The facilitator will also be responsible for managing learning&amp;nbsp;materials on Canvas and ensuring that all SDL content, lesson plans,assessments, student resources, and deliverables are properly migrated onto&amp;nbsp;Canvas before the start of in-person sessions. The candidate should therefore&amp;nbsp;have a strong working knowledge of online learning tools and products,&lt;br&gt;including learning management systems, digital collaboration tools, content&amp;nbsp;creation platforms, assessment tools, and student engagement technologies.&amp;nbsp;The candidate should also have a clear understanding of the ethical and&amp;nbsp;appropriate use of artificial intelligence in academic settings. This includes&amp;nbsp;awareness of academic integrity, responsible AI use, appropriate student&amp;nbsp;guidance on AI-supported learning, and the ability to help students use AI tools&amp;nbsp;in ways that strengthen rather than replace their thinking, research, writing, and&lt;br&gt;problem-solving skills.&lt;/p&gt;
